         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. commends Kohen's efforts for R. Joseph Ḥayyim's
                            yeshivah. But Z. had trouble Ḥayyim's reply to him: because he finds it
                            incredible that he is able to sustain ten people, as he claims and he
                            did not understand what materials Ḥayyim is teaching. 2. Shares his plan
                            that Kohen is to travel to the donations official Ergas in Livorno to
                            gather donations for the yeshivah which Z. and Kohen intend to establish
                            in the Holy Land. 3.In Z.'s opinion, the emissary of Safed wants to
                            prolong his stay in Livorno(?). 4. Z. intended "in the beginning" to
                            travel to the Holy Land – today he thinks the country poor and unsafe
                            and he has heard from the emissary of Jerusalem that men of rank are
                            being forced to gather donations for Jerusalem. Their wives would not be
                            able to withstand the living conditions. 5. Z. is enraged by the delayed
                            reply of Capsuto who also has plans to settle there. He asks Kohen to
                            tell Capsuto that he is waiting for a reply if he intends to write to
                            him. 6. Asks Kohen send him a Spanish olives.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">היתה לי טרנה בתשובתך</note>
